Not the worst burrito I've ever had but certainly not good.  We had the Supercarne y uno de al pastor.  The meat was dry and flavorless, the beans were flavorless, (not sure if there were any) the guacamole was not fresh, the lettuce tasted off and it was the wrong kind of lettuce.  There was no real sauce on the burrito, no pico de gallo, nada.  There was really nothing good about this burrito.  The only tasty thing they had was a housemade chipotle sauce.  I would not recommend their burritos.
